                    "systemPrompt": {
                        "id": "systemPrompt",
                        "type": "long-input",
                        "value": "You are a Jira ticket diagnosis agent for CRB (Customer Reported Bugs).\n\nYour job is to:\n- Read the ticket summary, description, comments, status and timeline.\n- Identify the real underlying cause in a compact technical phrase.\n- Identify the current status context in a short phrase.\n\nReturn ONLY a valid JSON in this exact format:\n{\n  \"cause\": \"<short technical reason, e.g. 'Webhook not received from vendor'>\",\n  \"status_context\": \"<short status phrase, e.g. 'still unassigned in To-Do' or 'in review' or 'fixed'>\"\n}\n\nRules:\n- \"cause\" must be concise and factual, no fluff.\n- \"status_context\" should describe ticket state in 3–7 words max.\n- Do not add explanation text outside JSON."
                    },
                    "userPrompt": {
                        "id": "userPrompt",
                        "type": "long-input",
                        "value": "Ticket data:\n\nTicket ID: <CRB_Analyzer_API.ticket_id>\nSummary: <CRB_Analyzer_API.summary>\nDescription: <CRB_Analyzer_API.description>\nStatus: <CRB_Analyzer_API.status>\nPriority: <CRB_Analyzer_API.priority>\nDays in status: <CRB_Analyzer_API.days_in_status>\nTotal days open: <CRB_Analyzer_API.total_days_open>\n\nRecent comments (latest first):\n<CRB_Analyzer_API.comments>\n\nUsing this information, fill the JSON fields exactly as requested in the system prompt. If the status is 'Cancelled' or 'Rejected', this is likely a false report."
                    },
